# Vercel Blob (Cart2Barrel)

Official overview: [Vercel Blob](https://vercel.com/docs/vercel-blob); SDK and uploads: [Using the Blob SDK](https://vercel.com/docs/storage/vercel-blob/using-blob-sdk), [server upload](https://vercel.com/docs/storage/vercel-blob/server-upload).

## Secrets and env

- **`BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN`** lives **only** in `.env` / Vercel project env. Never commit tokens or paste real values into rules, README, or tracked docs.
- Prefer **`getBlobReadWriteToken()`** / **`blobReadWriteNotConfiguredMessage()`** from `src/lib/vercel-blob-env.ts` so missing-token errors stay consistent.

## Where uploads run

- Perform **`put()`** from **`@vercel/blob`** inside **Server Actions** (or other trusted server code), not from the client with the write token exposed.
- After upload, persist the returned **`url`** (and any metadata you need) via **Drizzle** on the appropriate row — see `.cursor/rules/cart2barrel-drizzle-neon.mdc`.

## Access mode

- This app stores **public** blob URLs in Postgres (`access: 'public'`). Anyone with the URL can fetch the object; do **not** put secrets or pre‑authorized documents in public blobs.
- **Private** Blob stores need reads through your app (e.g. Route Handler + `get()`). If you switch a feature to private storage, design explicit authorization — see `.cursor/rules/cart2barrel-clerk-authz.mdc`.

## Pathnames (immutable uploads)

- Treat uploads as **immutable**: use **unique pathnames** (e.g. UUID segment per file), matching Vercel’s guidance to avoid overwrite/cache surprises.
- Do **not** rely on overwriting the same pathname unless you intentionally use `allowOverwrite` and understand **CDN/browser caching** (updates can lag; see Vercel Blob caching docs).

## Canonical path prefixes (this repo)

Keep prefixes stable so listings and ops stay predictable:

| Prefix | Use |
|--------|-----|
| `retailer-receipts/{orderItemId}/…` | Paid-line retailer receipt screenshots |
| `product-images/{itemRequestId}/…` | Customer product photo uploads |
| `warehouse-barcodes/{orderItemId}/…` | Inbound barcode photos |

## Authorization

- Every upload or DB update that attaches a blob URL must **verify the Clerk user** may modify that resource (**owner** or **admin**), scoped in Drizzle — same rules as other mutations (`.cursor/rules/cart2barrel-clerk-authz.mdc`).

## Validation

- Validate identifiers (**UUIDs**, etc.) with **Zod** at the trust boundary. Multipart/file uploads may use `FormData` internally, but **do not** type the exported action argument as `FormData` — extract fields, validate with Zod, then call `put()` (`.cursor/rules/cart2barrel-rsc-server-actions-zod.mdc`).

## Deletes

- Clearing a URL in the database **does not** delete the blob object. Use **`del()`** from `@vercel/blob` only when product intent is to remove storage; handle missing-token and idempotency as appropriate.

## UI

- File pickers and dialogs should use **shadcn/ui** patterns (`.cursor/rules/cart2barrel-shadcn-ui.mdc`). Prefer **`next/image`** only when `remotePatterns` (or equivalent) cover blob hosts; otherwise use documented alternatives (e.g. `<img>` for arbitrary blob URLs) without weakening CSP casually.
